The paper deals with the problem of obtaining strong coresets for clustering and subspace approximation problems, which are fundamental topics in computer science. The techniques used involve dimensionality reduction and optimization, which are common themes in several subfields of computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper involves information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SI) concepts, which are also relevant to the problem at hand.
